{
  "text": "The parasitological methodologies applied to cure control of Chagas disease include two categories referred to as (1) direct parasitological tests, including fresh-blood-examination (FBE) and trypomastigotes concentration (buffy coat, microhematocrit, and Strout tests) and (2) indirect parasitological tests, including xenodiagnosis and hemoculture [CITATION_1] .",
